                ║    Place the file in the SAME FOLDER as index.html.          ║
                ║                                                              ║
                ║    Your project structure should look like this:             ║
                ║                                                              ║
                ║    📁 your-project/   (= your repo root)                     ║
                ║    ├── 📄 index.html                                         ║
                ║    ├── 🖼️  juncala-forest-homepage.jpg   ← PUT IT HERE      ║
                ║    ├── 📁 css/                                               ║
                ║    ├── 📁 js/                                                ║
                ║    └── 📁 assets/                                            ║
                ║                                                              ║
                ║  On Netlify:                                                 ║
                ║    Your "Publish directory" in Site Settings > Build & Deploy║
                ║    must point to the folder containing index.html.           ║
                ║    Put the image in that same folder.                        ║
                ║    If Publish directory is blank or "." → repo root is fine. ║
